SEC_COMMENTS: Faculty Led Study Abroad.ýAfter arrival and exploration of the capital, Quito, studentsýwill journey to the Cloud Forest to begin work on a forestryýproject. This will involve working with the community to improveýquality of life through the sustainable use of natural resources.ýPossible activities include reforestation and seed collection,ýorganic gardening, dairy processing, and environmental education.ýAfter completing this project, students will visit LagunaýQuilotoa, an emerald lagoon inside a volcano, and a Pujiliýindigenous market on their way to the Amazon. There are twoýprojects that will be completed in the Amazon Rainforest; bothýfocus on conservation of the flora and fauna of the rainforest.ýThe first project has students working at the Animal WildlifeýRescue Center. Activities here may include rescue andýrehabilitation of animals, veterinary assistance, and education.ýFor the second Amazon project students will work at an ecologicalýresearch site where they will spend time on habitat work andýbehavioral monitoring activities. The weekend between projectsýwill give us the opportunity to visit the Swing at the End of theýWorld, the Baños Thermal Springs, and the Pailón del Diabloýwaterfall. The trip will conclude with a bus ride back to Quitoýfor departure home. Almost all meals and all lodging &ýtransportation in Ecuador are included.
